Date: Sat 27 Apr 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Click10.com, Fri 26 Apr 2002 [edited
<http://www.click10.com/mia/news/stories/news-142086720020426-130402.html>

Florida: West Nile Virus Found in Miami-Dade Horse
--------------------------------------------------
The Florida Department of Health says that it has a report of a horse
from Miami-Dade that is infected with West Nile virus. This is the
first time that the mosquito-borne virus has shown up in the county.
Last year the virus was found in birds in the county, but there were
no reports of it being transmitted to animals or people.
During 2001 there were 12 confirmed human cases of West Nile virus in
Florida. Most people have mild or no symptoms at all, however in
older people or those with other health issues, it can cause serious
illness and occasionally, death. Because the disease is transmitted
to humans by mosquitoes, the health department is advising Florida
residents to take extra precautions to prevent mosquito bites.
--
